            suited to you individually, but consider the following advantages of
            renting a bike while traveling.
          </p>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-900">
            <span class="text-xl">üîπ</span> It makes your life easier.
          </p>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-900">
            <span class="text-xl">üîπ</span> No worries about damaging your bike during
            transport.
          </p>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-900">
            <span class="text-xl">üîπ</span> No setting up your bicycle on the first
            day.
          </p>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-900">
            <span class="text-xl">üîπ</span> We select the MTB that suits you the
            best.
          </p>

          <p class="text-lg text-gray-900 mt-4">
            Very good reasons to travel with your bike.
          </p>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-900">Comfortable and confident:</p>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-900">
            <span class="text-xl">üîπ</span> You are focused on performance.
          </p>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-900">
            <span class="text-xl">üîπ</span> You‚Äôre confident in handling your bike.
          </p>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-900">
            <span class="text-xl">üîπ</span> It could save money.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div>
          <img
            class="rounded-xl hidden md:block"
            src="/cycle-tour/roadbike/roadbike-escape-granada/rb-eg-product.webp"
            alt=""
          />
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 md:gap-12 mt-10">
        <div class="mb-6 md:mb-20">
          <h2
            class="max-w-2xl md:px-0 font-bold text-4xl md:text-5xl xl:text-6xl">
            Road Bike
          </h2>
          <Dots class="mb-4" />
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-900 mb-2">
            Check our BLOG CYCLING article ‚ÄúOur Bicycle Selection‚Äù to see your
            Road Bike. We provide 3 high-quality Full Carbon Road Bikes. When
            booking, you indicate your height and weight so that the bicycle's
            frame size is correct at the start of your tour.
          </p>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-900">
            <span class="text-xl">üîπ</span> We help you fit your pedals or saddle
            if you'd like to bring them.
          </p>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-900">
            <span class="text-xl">üîπ</span> We provide low-range gearing suited to
            mountainous terrain.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="mb-6 md:mb-20">
          <h2
            class="max-w-2xl md:px-0 font-bold text-4xl md:text-5xl xl:text-6xl">
            Level
          </h2>
          <Dots class="mb-4" />
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-900 mb-2">
            The route type and difficulty are based on your fitness level and
            technical skills. Before booking the ‚ÄúRoad Bike Trails Granada,‚Äù
            please fill out a questionnaire form to tailor your itinerary to the
            right level. After receiving your questionnaire, we send you an MTB
            Bike route with technical information.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Button to download PDF -->
      <section class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
        <div>
          <div>
            <h2 class="md:px-0 font-bold text-4xl md:text-5xl xl:text-6xl">
              Cancellation Policy
            </h2>
            <Dots class="mb-4" />
          </div>

          <div>
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 mt-1">See Terms and Conditions.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h2
            class="max-w-2xl md:px-0 font-bold text-4xl md:text-5xl xl:text-6xl">
            Recommendations
          </h2>
          <Dots class="mb-4" />
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-900">
            <span class="text-xl">üîπ</span> Explore the city of Granada in the afternoon
            with some tapas or experience a Flamenco show in the evening.
          </p>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-900">
            <span class="text-xl">üîπ</span> Join a guided Alhambra tour, a palace
            and fortress monument of Islamic architecture. (World Heritage Site by
            UNESCO)
          </p>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-900">
            <span class="text-xl">üîπ</span> Visit the Oil Mill Interpretation Centre
            with various routes where you can discover the culture of olive oil.
          </p>
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-900">
            <span class="text-xl">üîπ</span> You don't have to organize anything.
            We handle your reservations to meet your needs If you are interested
            in one of these recommendations or any other activity.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>
      <div
        class="grid bg-[#0E46A3] place-items-center border-spacing-3 backdrop-blur-sm w-fit m-auto md:px-28 p-10 mt-24 rounded-xl shadow-[0px_0px_23px_14px_#00000024]">
        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-center text-gray-200">
          More information about our tour
        </h2>
        <Link
          style="muted"
          href="/cycle-tour/roadbike/roadbike-escape-granada/ROAD BIKE ESCAPE GRANADA.pdf"
          download="Road Bike Escape Granada"
          class="flex gap-1 items-center justify-center mt-8 font-semibold"
          rel="noopener">
          View trip notes
        </Link>
      </div>

      <!-- Slider Photos -->
      <section class="m-auto md:w-full rounded-xl md:px-8 md:py-20">
        <ol class="relative mt-16">
          {(<SliderReact IMG={IMG} client:visible />)}
        </ol>
      </section>

      <!--  TimeLine per days  -->
      <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl xl:text-6xl md:p-4 mt-16 font-bold mb-4">
        What to expect
      </h2>
      <p class="text-gray-700 text-lg mt-4 md:px-4">
        Granada is a perfect cycling getaway destination, excellent for a
        cycling holiday.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 text-lg mt-4 md:px-4">
        There is an infinity of cycle routes for all levels from beginners to
        advanced cyclists with different gradient climbs of varying lengths and
        a huge variety of elevation profiles through an area with a great
        diversity of landscapes from rolling hills, pine forests, deserts, and
        mountains to the tropical coast. The roads are well-surfaced with little
        traffic in a mountainous region with popular mountain passes and iconic
        climbs where professionals come to train on these great roads such as
        the Sierra Nevada Stage which is one of the great climbs in Spain and
        has been selected for several times during ‚ÄúLa Vuelta‚Äù, Tour of Spain,
        as a Grand Tour Summit Finish on the highest paved road in Europe.
      </p>
      <p class="text-gray-700 text-lg mt-4 md:px-4">
